    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "Recto: Official letter mentioning an am\u012br (l.2). The sender seems to complain that he did not receive a reply to his letter to the addressee (l. 1). The letter ends with blessings for the addressee (l. 5).\n\u00a0\nVerso: The papyrus is reused for a list of expenses consisting of agricultural products, Coptic and Muslim names, dates and Greek numerals. Payments are made in wheat (qam\u1e25) and barley (sha\u02bf\u012br), and for someone\u2019s living expenses (rizq, l. 9). The account\u2019s entries were written at different occasions. Traces of earlier writing are visible before line 4 and at the end of line 7."
    },
    {
      "label": "Diacritical dots",
      "value": "There are no diacritical dots"
    }
